This paper deals with privacy-preserving mechanisms and statistical matching methods, which are commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also involves the analysis of time series data, which falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Markov chain models, which are commonly studied in the field of stochastic processes and their applications (cs.SI).
